# Datamodel.ai — Cursor Rules

## Model instructions
- You are operating as a senior Next.js/TypeScript engineer
- Always read .cursorrules before generating any code
- When in doubt, ask before writing — do not assume scope
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Never generate code that contradicts .cursorrules

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router — Server Components and Server Actions only
- PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM — JSONB for CDM/UDM data
- Clerk — org-aware multi-tenant auth
- Inngest — all background jobs
- Claude API via Vercel AI SDK — generateObject + Zod only
- shadcn/ui + Tailwind

## Non-negotiable rules

1. Server Actions for ALL mutations — never use API routes for mutations
2. generateObject + Zod for ALL AI structured output — never parse raw text
3. Inngest for ALL background jobs — never block API routes with sync
4. org_id on EVERY DB query — never query without tenant scope
5. Drizzle `with:` for relations — no N+1 queries
6. revalidatePath after EVERY mutation
7. One migration per story — never bundle schema changes
8. Verification script per story — scripts/verify-s{N}.{N}.ts
9. status = 'production' filter at DB layer — not in application code
10. No hardcoded secrets — process.env only
11. Exponential backoff on all connector API calls
12. All sync operations logged to sync_logs

## Auth pattern (every server action)
const { orgId, userId } = await auth();
if (!orgId || !userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

## DB query pattern (every query)
await db.query.tableName.findMany({
  where: and(eq(table.orgId, orgId), ...otherConditions),
});

## AI pattern
import { generateObject } from 'ai';
import { z } from 'zod';
const { object } = await generateObject({
  model: anthropic(DEFAULT_MODEL),
  schema: MyZodSchema,
  prompt: '...',
});

## File structure
- lib/actions/ — one file per domain (e.g. fields.ts, sources.ts)
- lib/db/schema/ — one file per entity group
- lib/connectors/ — one folder per source
- lib/inngest/functions/ — one file per job
- scripts/ — verify-s{N}.{N}.ts per story

## DESIGN SYSTEM

1. COLORS — Never use Tailwind color utilities directly (BAD: bg-gray-800, text-blue-500 / GOOD: bg-background, bg-card, text-foreground, text-primary). Exception: status indicators (text-green-400, text-red-400) OK inline.

2. TYPOGRAPHY — Never use arbitrary font sizes (BAD: text-[13px] / GOOD: text-xs, text-sm). Headings: font-semibold tracking-tight. Muted: text-muted-foreground. Mono: font-mono for field_keys, IDs, code.

3. ELEVATION — Borders over shadows in dark mode (BAD: shadow-md / GOOD: border border-border + bg layering). Layer order: bg-background → bg-card → bg-popover → bg-muted.

4. SPACING — Tailwind scale only (BAD: p-[14px] / GOOD: p-3, p-4, gap-2, gap-3).

5. DARK MODE — always active (html.dark). Never design for light first. Never bg-white.

6. INTERACTIONS — Hover: duration-150 ease. Selected: border-primary/60 bg-primary/5. Disabled: opacity-40 cursor-not-allowed.

7. COMPONENTS — Buttons: size variants only. Cards: rounded-xl. Inputs: h-9 bg-transparent border-input. Badges: semantic variants for status.

## What NOT to do
- No client-side data fetching (no useEffect + fetch)
- No direct db instantiation outside lib/db/index.ts
- No AI calls that return raw text and parse with regex
- No sync work in API routes
- No queries without org_id scope
- No hard deletes — status = 'deprecated' always
- No field reaches production without approved_by + approved_at set
- Agents only ever read status = 'production' fields — enforced at DB layer

## Git Workflow — follow after every story

After every story verify script passes:
  git add .
  git commit -m "feat(story-id): brief description"
  git push origin main

Commit message format:
  feat(s0.2): org schema + multi-tenancy
  feat(design.1): design system — dark mode + indigo tokens
  fix(s0.6): hubspot pagination edge case
  chore(infra): update env vars

Rules:
  - Never commit .env.local or node_modules
  - Always run npm run build before pushing
  - Push to main → Vercel auto-deploys in ~30 seconds
  - Check production URL after every deploy